The paper discusses a new track for TREC 2019 focused on ad hoc ranking in a large data regime, with a particular emphasis on deep learning methods. The paper includes a large amount of technical detail on the data sets used and the performance of various methods, suggesting that it is likely to be of interest to researchers in information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
